      "message": "\u003e Let\u0027s get rid of this manufacturer matches folder stuff for now and let\u0027s start with a manufacturer match existing. If we have to make all these regex contortions to figure it out then it will be hard for folks to figure out why their changes are failing.\n\nNot interested in that.  The manufacturer matches stuff works as written, and as a maintainer I believe this script will help me maintain the folder structure.\n\nGiven the number of violations of this on code that was at one point reviewed, we need to have some kind of automation, and burn down list.\n\n\u003e \n\n\u003e Overall the parsing here is conceptually wrong anyways since `Probe` is supposed to represent a boolean-ish conditional which needs an AST and proper parsing.\n\nAgreed, this makes assumptions about the parsing, but I believe them to be correct assumptions that we will use positive matches, not NOT in a FRU probe.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e Creating complicated regex to work around that is an unstable shortcut which will likely introduce problems later on.\n\n\nCan you be more specific about the potential problems and what you think we should do here instead?  This is only a CI script.  If we have problems, we can always disable it (temporarily or permanently)",
